    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>In these regions the avalanche danger is high (level 4).</highlights>
      <comment>Heavy snowfall. The wind will be moderate to strong. &lt;br/> The snowpack remains in most cases unstable. Natural avalanches are possible over a wide area. Avalanches can penetrate deep layers reach very large size. &lt;br/> Without question, it is inadvisable to engage in backcountry touring.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>Somewhat older wind slabs remain for the foreseeable future prone to triggering. As a consequence of new snow and wind, further wind slabs will form. &lt;br/> Numerous weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
